## Architecture

```
Layer 5  Superpowers + GSD  --> Engineering discipline + execution orchestration
Layer 4  x.ospec CLI        --> Spec automation (optional)
Layer 3  changes/            --> Change packages (proposal/design/tasks)
Layer 2  specs/              --> Long-lived living specs
Layer 1  repo + git          --> Foundation
```

## Project Structure

```
{{ project_name }}/
├── README.md
├── AGENTS.md                         <-- AI agent rules
├── docs/
│   ├── engineering-principles.md     <-- Definition of Done & standards
│   └── superpowers.md                <-- Superpowers + GSD guide
├── xospec/
│   ├── specs/                        <-- Living specs by capability
│   └── changes/                      <-- Change packages
└── .planning/
    ├── PROJECT.md                    <-- GSD project context
    ├── ROADMAP.md                    <-- Phase-based execution plan
    └── STATE.md                      <-- Current progress tracking
```

## Workflow

1. Check `.planning/ROADMAP.md` for current phase
2. Read `xospec/changes/<change-id>/proposal.md`
3. Draft `design.md` and `tasks.md`
4. Implement one task at a time (TDD)
5. Update specs after behavior changes
6. Update `.planning/STATE.md` on phase completion
7. Open PR — review spec first, code second
